The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Hindi in UN

 New York, July 13 (PTI): Prime Minister Manmohan Singh has promised to take forceful action to make Hindi an official language at the UN.

 Singh, in a message to the eighth World Hindi Conference, said the government is working in this direction after the earlier global Hindi meets put forward the proposal. 




